Rating: 4
This dish is awesome. Although we some flavorful additions (venison sausage and roasted tomatoes) I am confident that the wonderful combination and proportions of the herbs and rich flavors with the fresh veggies will be just as satisfying when I try it again without the additions. Except for the additions, I followed the recipe and was very happy happy with the flavor and spice. It didn't require additional salt and pepper on the table!

Rating: 3
I give this recipe 3 forks but that is after my alterations! Lots of reviewers said it was tastless so I sauteed 4-5 slices of bacon to start. Then I made it as suggested using fresh herbs. When it was done it was really dull. I added 2-3 spoonfulls of tomato paste, dried chillies and salt. It ended up as very tasty. Next time I would use more bacon.

Rating: 3
instead of broth I used white wine and butter. This intensified the flavor. I also added a scotch bonnet pepper which gave it the zip it needed. A very healthy dish.

