Rating: 3
Pretty good. I made with extra pine nuts, extra broth(a whole can) and extra salt (it needed it). Agree it could have used the crushed red pepper; was a little bland without. I too used fresh herbs and would do the same again. Served with garlic bread and a tossed green salad with blue cheese and strawberries. Yum!

Rating: 3
This is a wonderful vegetarian dish that I have made several times for company. My only criticism is that it is slightly too dry, so I add a bit of extra broth.

Rating: 4
Fabulous!!! It needed more broth to saute than originally called for and I used fresh not dried herbs (3 tsp fresh = 1 tsp dried) I also cut the pasta down to 1/2 pd as my husband and I tend to like additional sauce. I used walnuts instead of pine nuts (it's what I had available) Will make it again for company the same way. FABULOUS!! Tasty!! Great dish.

